<h3>Libraries</h3>

<h4>Melville J. Herskovitz Library of African Studies</h4>

<p>The Herskovits Library is a reliable site for identifying African poetry in the US. The search engine is useful and the holding appears to be fairly up to date as it includes the most recent APBF titles. Its archive of antiquities is also handy, though not for this purpose. It is a useful way to confirm publication records of African poets.</p>

